Actress Mary Njoku has challenged men on the need to maintain the same energy they exerted when they were still dating their partners even after marriage. Njoku, in an Instagram post, shared a collage of a lady with one photo bearing the caption: “When she was your GF” and the other “When she is your wife.” The lady as a ‘single’ person looked well cared for and prettier than she when she assumed the status of a ‘wife’ which prompted the filmmaker’s assertion.   Reactions as Pastor sprays Davido pounds     Joe Budden, Nicki Minaj urge Grammys to make Wizkid’s…     Oxlade signs new deal with Columbia Records   The mother of two explained a wife’s condition mirrors the true personality of her husband to the world. “Dear MEN. The condition of your wife shows the world the kind of man you are”, she wrote. “Your daughter cannot be your princess if her mother is not a queen. “So take a deep look at your wife and ask yourself, what kind of man are you?”